Kinh nghiệm 1 năm ở vị trí Content Fanpage;
Có laptop cá nhân;
Tốt nghiệp ĐH truyền thông, Marketing, báo chí…;
Có khả năng thiết kế cơ bản;
Có khả năng lập kế hoạch, tổng hợp, báo cáo;
Nhanh nhẹn, có tư duy tốt, nhạy bén;
Có khả năng phối hợp làm việc theo đội nhóm
Thời gian làm việc:
8h - 17h30; từ Thứ 2 - Thứ 7 (Nghỉ 4 CN)

4434626065.description:
Position Overview
A Social Studies Teacher is responsible for teaching, preparing materials & arranging schedules, organizing activities, tests or assessments relating to Social Studies; as well as ensuring the quality of classes and assessments. He/she is also required to join the tasks of the Academic Team, contribute, and generate ideas to the general teaching.
Responsibilities & Duties
Teaching tasks
Collaborate with Lead Teacher to build up the Academic Year's plan for Social Studies Team, Academic Team & personal plan;
Prepare materials, lesson plans, teaching plans with specific learning goals relating to Social Studies for students;
Teach, manage and take care of students during your classes;
Organize teaching and learning activities to develop students' learning capacity;
Create new teaching or learning methods to help students achieve their best results;
Update class's status and students individually (if any) on Learning Management System of the School;
Organize Social Studies assessments or tests to evaluate students' learning effectiveness and proactively adjust teaching methods;
Complete the academic reports assigned by the Senior Leadership Team;
Prepare materials and join mutual meetings or 1-1 meeting with parents of your class;
Carry out other duties such as student supervision, lunch duties, club activities, after-school activities (ASA), and advisory tasks as required.
Non-teaching tasks
Collaborate with teachers, students, and faculty on implementing initiatives that enhance academic performance and student engagement;
Actively participate in training and professional development activities required/organized by the School;
Build respectful, cooperative relationships with Parents and Students;
Participate in school activities and events;
Support admissions/marketing events for student recruitment;
Carry out WASC assignment and MOET related work as required.
Other tasks as required by the Academic Team, Senior Leadership Team, and Board of Management.
Job Requirements
Bachelor's/Master's degree in Education, majoring in Social Studies or related subjects.
Advanced degree or specialization training that supports the teaching role is preferred;
Proven experience teaching in a school setting;
Knowledge of and experience in using a variety of assessments and differentiated learning techniques;
Grounded in knowledge about teaching and learning;
Effective communicator- communicate well with a diverse community, proficient in writing skills;
Highly skilled at using technology;
Strong organizational and time management skills.
Benefits
Premium healthcare insurance package;
Up to 76 days of paid leave per year (including public holidays, annual leave, sick leave, summer, autumn, and winter breaks)
Tuition fee exemption for staff's children;
Free lunch, gym, swimming pool;
International professional working environment.

